The course will deal with the basics of economic policies, history and formation of economic theories, and the formation of modern economics and social structure.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of this course is to introduce the formation of different economic theories and policies, acting mechanisms of economics, the formation of the modern economy and social organization, and the role of the local level in economic issues.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the course: *	Has an overview of the general acting mechanisms and basics of economy; *	Knows the system and basic concepts of economic policy; *	Knows the history and formation of economic theory and the basic concepts of different economic orders; *	Knows the roles of the institutions that shape a country's economic policy; *	Is knowledgeable about local municipalities' economic role and local economic policies; *	Knows the basics of law regarding local municipalities in the economics field. A student who has passed the course can: *	Understand the cause and effect of economic-political decisions; *	Evaluate the impact of different economic-political fields to entrepreneurship, local government and central government; *	Evaluate the application of different models and approaches in the context of different levels of government in Estonia; *	Navigate transitional economy models in modern context; *	Differentiate local government legal issues on other levels.
